I will not return! I am an African-American man.  Went on 9/23/2020 with my fiancé to grab some subs as we have done in the past. The shop was empty besides ourselves and the workers, as is typical on a Wednesday evening these days. Each one looked me in my eye and said nothing. Not a hello, can I help you, would you like to place an order? Nothing. Being the optimist I am, I figured I may not be standing in the right spot, but also suspected a force I’m all to familiar with, as a Black man, was at work.  I positioned myself directly in front of the counter and all the workers went to the back. It was if they were intentionally refusing us service. We continued to stand there and we even conversed about our orders louder than necessary to make clear we were ready. I stood in that same spot for 10 minutes, nothing but me, mine, and the workers. Still no service. We left in complete dismay.  We quickly returned wanting clarity on this very unusual behavior. We inquired if we needed to place an order prior to coming. At that point the workers asked what did we want? Of course we weren’t about to spend our Black dollars in any establishment that treated us as second class citizens. We attempted to explain our frustration, but the workers informed us that they were to busy and we could either place an order or leave. Utterly disgusted and successfully repelled by the apparent prejudice by the white workers, we left. We will never return.

Isabella's is simply amazing. Don't let the pedestrian location deter you, for the food is anything but. I came here on a trip to the inner harbor, and I have to say, this little shop simply blew me away. I got an Aria sandwich, which has chicken, mushrooms, cheese and pesto inside it. The quality and taste of the pesto was unlike anything I've ever had before. Simply exquisite. And the chicken. The texture of the chicken was an experience for my tongue. The sandwich itself was an experience I never expected to find in Baltimore. For the casual tourist, or the commuting local, this restaurant is a must visit. The reasonable prices combined with the extremely high quality food makes Isabella's the place to be if you must satisfy your cravings, or even just for a quick bite.

I just got the Jersey Boy sub, and when I tell you it was good.  Seasoned, simmered greens and italian sausage.  Goood!!!
The Scooch.
Best pizza in the area. Great staff. Had a really good time there.

The bread and quality meats and cheeses make Isabella's the BEST place for a sandwich in downtown Baltimore!  Their brick oven pizzas will put most others to shame, with smooth sauce and perfectly balanced crust.  Daniel Stewart is a master at preparing many of the Italian specialties, including fresh sausage, most meatballs, and arancini that will change your life...
The Saraceno pizza blew me away with its simplicity and big flavor.  DaPatro got approval from my daughter, the pizza monster.  We stuffed ourself without deflating our wallet.  Great place!
This is fantastic pizza, the best in Baltimore. The place is really small, but the food is so good. And they're right across the street from Vaccaro for dessert. Amazing.

Yep totally agree with Leo below. I'm from Windsor and their pizza equally rivals some of the best pizza you can get in my hometown.  Had the prosciutto/gorgonzola/walnut and also the capicolla/garlic. Both were incredible and the crust was just perfect.

This is the best pizza in the universe. no better pizza is possible. the crust, the sauce, the cheese and toppings -- everything is world-class. the pizzas are made fresh and served straight out of the oven. your search is over now.
Fast, Friendly, amazing quality ingredients. I am told you can BYOB if you want to eat in.
Fresh, great thin crust,  and reasonably priced given the high quality.

Possibly the best i've ever had! Maybe even better than La Zingara in Windsor Ont.  I cant remember the names, but we had the sub with ham and rosemary, the 4 meat pizza and the pizza with ripini and sopressata [about $50 total with 3 drinks]. Each of the 3 were outstanding, the ripini and sopressata was out of this world.  I love they make their own cheese. Not a lot of seats, but that gave it a very snug, warm and old world feel.

Damn they can make a great sandwich. When I came to Isabella's, all sandwiches are beyond good, makes me wonder why I can not make a delicious sandwich at home. They have some good bread, it is a perfect balance between crisp but tender. It's crisp enough to hold up the oil, keeping the sandwich together, feeling great when they come on my mouth.

The Isabella sandwich is unbelievable.  It's the only thing I've had besides getting some olives to go and I bought my dad a crazy good bottle of olive oil.  The owner is very knowledgable and will talk your ear off.  No room to eat inside so take it out.  Really cute girls make your food by the way.
Pizza was delicious!!!  I would take it out as opposed to dining in...not a lot of room in there..
Fantastic... enough said. My favorite are the subs, I have never had a bad sub and you will not find subs like them anywhere else!
delicious pizza!!
This place is mediocre at best. The customer service is lacking and condescending attitudes are disgusting. I would not not recommend this joint to anyone.
Amazing brick oven pizza and sandwiches!!  Not really a place to dine in, grab and go. A few small tables.

We were on a weekend trip to Baltimore and as soon as we parked, we were overwhelmed with the delicious aroma of fresh pizza. We wandered around the area trying to figure out where it came from and came across Isabella's.  Inside is *tiny* (literally 3 tables with very, very little seating room available) so if you can take it to go, that's probably your best bet. We did not really have that option but I am really glad we gave it a try. I am originally from NJ but have been living in TX and VA for the past 12 years; finding good authentic Italian food, specifically pizza, has been... a challenge, to say the least. My fiance is from TX so he was shocked to see what real pizza is supposed to be like!!! This definately hit the spot. Great pie, good price, super-friendly employees.  We loved it so much we went back for lunch the next day (my fiance's request, actually!!!); we got another pie as well as a cheesesteak hoagie for later, which was also yummy. Definately recommend and will definately go back next time we're in the area.
